# Module 2: dbt and the Analytics Development Lifecycle (ADLC)

## What is the ADLC?

The Analytics Development Lifecycle is the end-to-end process 
of building, deploying and maintaining data pipelines — the 
data equivalent of DevOps in software engineering.

dbt is the tool that makes the ADLC possible by bringing 
software engineering best practices to analytics.

---

## The ADLC — 7 stages in an infinite loop

DEVELOP → PLAN → DEPLOY → TEST → ANALYZE → DISCOVER → OBSERVE → OPERATE
↑                                                                 │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

### Left side — Development (blue/green)

| Stage | What happens | dbt tool |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| **DEVELOP** | Write SQL models and transformations | dbt Core / dbt Cloud IDE |
| **PLAN** | Design data architecture and dependencies | dbt DAG (lineage graph) |
| **DEPLOY** | Run dbt in production automatically | dbt Cloud jobs |
| **TEST** | Validate data quality automatically | dbt tests (unique, not_null, etc.) |

### Right side — Operations (yellow/green)

| Stage | What happens | dbt tool |
|-------|-------------|----------|
| **ANALYZE** | Explore transformed data in BI tools | Power BI · Tableau · Looker |
| **DISCOVER** | Find new insights and business questions | dbt Explorer |
| **OBSERVE** | Monitor data quality and performance | dbt observability |
| **OPERATE** | Keep pipelines running and maintained | dbt Cloud orchestration |

